38c-58a4-11e4-8264-deed989ae9a2_story.html</ref>\n* [[Steve Ricchetti]], former Deputy Chief of Staff to President [[Bill Clinton]]<ref>[http://centeroncongress.org/steve-ricchetti Steve Ricchetti: President, Ricchetti, Inc.], Center for Congress at [[Indiana University]] (accessed April 5, 2016).</ref>\n* [[Denise Turner Roth]], Administrator of the [[General Services Administration|U.S. General Services Administration]] (GSA)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gsa.gov/portal/content/100046 |title=Denise Turner Roth \u2013 Administrator |publisher=Gsa.gov |accessdate=February 1, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126011335/http://www.gsa.gov/portal/content/100046 |archivedate=January 26, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Karl Rove]], former Deputy Chief of Staff to President [[George W. Bush]]<ref>The Washington Post. Retrieved from https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/karl-rove/gIQAUrlsAP_print.html</ref>\n* [[Rhea Seehorn]], actress best known for playing Kim Wexler on [[Better Call Saul]].<ref>Owen, R. (February 1, 2015). Richmond native Vince Gilligan back with prequel to \"Breaking Bad\". Richmond Times-Dispatch. Retrieved from http://www.richmond.com/entertainment/television/richmond-native-vince-gilligan-back-with-prequel-to-breaking-bad/article_207e45b9-3624-5d4e-8219-9d6e69e72138.html</ref>\n* [[Martin Andrew Taylor]], former senior executive Corporate VP of [[Windows Live]] and [[MSN]], Chief of Staff to former [[Microsoft]] CEO [[Steve Ballmer]]<ref>{{Cite news |author=Dudley Brier |title=Plugged in to Microsoft's biggest rival |url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/businesstechnology/2002237511_msftlinux11.html |work=Seattle Times |date=April 11, 2005 |accessdate=October 31, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Chris Widger]], former Major League Baseball player [[Seattle Mariners]], [[Chicago White Sox]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.milb.com/player/index.jsp?player_id=124234|title=Chris Widger Stats, Highlights, Bio &#124; MiLB.com Stats &#124; The Official Site of Minor League Baseball|website=MiLB.com}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[George Mason University's historical hoaxes]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Spoken Wikipedia|George_Mason_University.ogg|2006-01-16}}\n* {{Official website}}\n\n{{-}}\n{{George Mason University}}\n{{Navboxes\n|titlestyle = {{CollegePrimaryStyle|George Mason Patriots |color = white }}\n|list =\n{{George Mason}}\n{{Colleges and universities in Virginia}}\n{{Southeastern Universities Research Association}}\n{{Atlantic 10 Conference navbox}}\n{{Eastern Wrestling League}}\n{{WGI_Independent_World_Drum_Lines}}\n{{Fairfax County, Virginia topics}}\n}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1949]]\n[[Category:1949 establishments in Virginia]]\n[[Category:George Mason]]\n[[Category:George Mason University| ]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Virginia]]\n[[Category:Education in Fairfax County, Virginia]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges accredited by the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools]]\n[[Category:Education in Arlington County, Virginia]]\n[[Category:Education in Prince William County, Virginia]]\n[[Category:Education in Loudoun County, Virginia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Public liberal arts and research university in Fairfax, Virginia}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name = George Mason University <br> \uc870\uc9c0\uba54\uc774\uc2a8\ub300\ud559\uad50\n| image_name = George Mason University logo.svg\n| image_size = 200\n| motto = Freedom and Learning\n| established = October 1, 1949<ref name=\"Finley\" />{{rp|5}} <br> ([[University of Virginia]])\n| type = [[Public University]] <br> [[Research University]]\n| academic_affiliations = [[Association of Public and Land-grant Universities|APLU]]<br />[[Oak Ridge Associated Universities|ORAU]]<br />[[Southeastern Universities Re